Class MOR3DArray

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Array3D.SemanticMap<MORDescriptor>, Array3D.SemanticMap.Resources<MORDescriptor,java.lang.String>, Semantics.Logger

    public class MOR3DArray
extends Array3D
implements Array3D.SemanticMap.Resources<MORDescriptor,java.lang.String>
    A semantically mappable Array3D based on aMOR library.

    It describes the semantic property of each components of the array as an OWLDataProperty, referee by name. Thus, the 'T' parameter of the Array3D.SemanticMap.Resources interface is set to: String. On the other hand the 'D' parameter is set to MORDescriptor, the object that will map a property name, given as a String, to an OWLDataProperty.

    Also, it implements the Array3D.SemanticMap interface by defining how a general 3D array should be semantically map in an ontology.

    REMARK: see here for more about the aMOR library.

      • writeSemantics

        public Semantics.WritingState writeSemantics(MORDescriptor semantic)
        This method relies on MORDescriptor.writeLiteral(String, OWLDataProperty, OWLLiteral) and Semantics.WritingState.merge(Semantics.WritingState) for writing this 3D array on the OWL ontology, described by the input parameter, and keep track of the computation state.

        In particular, it sequentially add the flowing semantic entities to the individual ('I'), described by MORDescriptor, and returns as soon as a writing state results to be: ! Semantics.WritingState#isOK().

        • I = hasXcomponent:x (getXproperty(), getXliteral(MORDescriptor)),
        • I = hasYcomponent:y (getYproperty(), getYliteral(MORDescriptor)),
        • I = hasZcomponent:z (getZproperty(), getZliteral(MORDescriptor)),

        REMARK: so far, the Semantics.MappingState.INCONSISTENT state is not managed (never returned) by this method.

        Specified by:
        writeSemantics in interface Array3D.SemanticMap<MORDescriptor>
        Parameters:
        semantic - the object that can manipulate the ontology and try to synchronise the java representation with the semantic structure.
        Returns:
        the state of the writing process undertaken.
        See Also:
        Array3D.SemanticMap#writeSemantics(Semantics.Descriptor)

      • readSemantics

        public Semantics.ReadingState readSemantics(MORDescriptor semantic)
        This method relies on MORDescriptor.readLiteral(String, OWLDataProperty, OWLLiteral) and Semantics.ReadingState.merge(Semantics.ReadingState) for reading this 3D array from the OWL ontology, described by the input parameter, and keep track of the computation state.

        In particular, it sequentially reads the flowing semantic entities from the individual ('I'), described by MORDescriptor, and returns as soon as a reading state results to be: ! Semantics.WritingState#isOK().

        • x = I(hasXcomponent) (getXproperty(), Array3D.setX(double)),
        • y = I(hasYcomponent) (getYproperty(), Array3D.setY(double)),
        • z = I(hasZcomponent) (getZproperty(), Array3D.setZ(double)),

        REMARK: so far, the Semantics.MappingState.INCONSISTENT state is not managed (never returned) by this method.

        Specified by:
        readSemantics in interface Array3D.SemanticMap<MORDescriptor>
        Parameters:
        semantic - the object that can manipulate the ontology and try to synchronise the java representation with the semantic structure.
        Returns:
        the state of the writing process undertaken.
        See Also:
        Array3D.SemanticMap#writeSemantics(Semantics.Descriptor)
